<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ871231-0144 </DOCNO><HL> UST Unit Slates Sale</HL><DD> 12/31/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> USTTENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM) </IN><DATELINE> GREENWICH, Conn.  </DATELINE><TEXT>   UST Inc.'s U.S. Tobacco Co. unit agreed to sell its House of Windsor subsidiary to a management team from the two units.    Terms weren't disclosed.    House of Windsor, Yoe, Pa., produces and markets smoking tobacco, leaf tobacco and cigars. Last year, its sales totaled about $13 million, which UST said makes up less than 3% of its consolidated sales. U.S. Tobacco produces and markets smokeless tobacco and imports pipes and pipe tobacco. </TEXT></DOC>